#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 49"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "49. Senāvāsasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on staying with armies"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.106"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.49.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.377"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa995"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sati karaṇīye senaṃ gantvā "
"atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six went to the army on some "
"business, and they stayed there for more than three nights."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā senāya vasissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics stay with the army?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa "
"kāraṇā senāya paṭivasāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s our misfortune that we must stay with the army for the sake of our "
"livelihood and because of our wives and children.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa996"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissantī”ti … pe "
"…"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six stay with the army for more than "
"three nights?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you stay with the army for more than three nights?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa997"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: dirattatirattaṃ → dviratta … (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"“Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāya, dirattatirattaṃ "
"tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If that monk has a reason for going to the army, he may stay with the army "
"for two or three nights."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vaseyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he stays longer than that, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "(<em>49</em>:<strong>98</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.49.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.49.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa998"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāyāti"
msgstr "If that monk has a reason for going to the army:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "siyā paccayo siyā karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "if he has a reason, if he has business."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.378"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa999"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Dirattatirattaṃ tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbanti"
msgstr "He may stay with the army for two or three nights:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "dvetisso rattiyo vasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may stay for two or for three nights."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1000"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vaseyyāti"
msgstr "If he stays longer than that:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "catutthe divase atthaṅgate sūriye senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he is staying with the army at sunset on the fourth day, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.49.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1001"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Atirekatiratte atirekasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than three nights, and he perceives it as more, and he is "
"staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Atirekatiratte vematiko senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than three nights, but he is unsure if it is, and he is "
"staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Atirekatiratte ūnakasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than three nights, but he perceives it as less, and he is "
"staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1002"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than three nights, but he perceives it as more, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than three nights, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than three nights, and he perceives it as less, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.107"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.49.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1003"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "dvetisso rattiyo vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays for two or three nights;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "ūnakadvetisso rattiyo vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays for less than two or three nights;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "dve rattiyo vasitvā tatiyāya rattiyā purāruṇā nikkhamitvā puna vasati,"
msgstr ""
"if he stays for two nights, then leaves before dawn on the third night, and "
"then stays again;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "gilāno vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays because he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "gilānassa karaṇīyena vasati,"
msgstr ""
"if he stays because there is something to be done for someone who is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "senā vā paṭisenāya ruddhā hoti,"
msgstr " if the army is obstructed by an enemy army;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "kenaci palibuddho hoti,"
msgstr "if he is obstructed from leaving;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1004"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "Senāvāsasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on staying with armies, is finished."

